title: 5 adults injured in shooting on Plymouth Ave N in Minneapolis
content:
MINNEAPOLIS (KMSP) - Five people were injured in a shooting early Sunday morning in north Minneapolis, according to police.
The shooting happened at 1717 Plymouth Avenue North around 12:30 am.
The five adult victims, three men and two women, all received non-life threatening injuries. One man was shot in the lower torso, another was shot in the arm and the third man was hit in the leg. One woman was wounded in the buttock, the other woman was shot in the leg.
5 adults injured in shooting on Plymouth Ave N in Minneapolis
Police believe the victim and the shooter know each other.
The case is still under investigation.
